Hi All,

Thanks for your time on Monday. Quick follow up on my actions:

Obstacle NOTAM rules - I have pasted screenshots (sorry!) below of our obst=
acle NOTAM filtering rules in Outlook. The subject line corresponds to the =
NOTAM Q-Code and the Body is the body of the NOTAM. The ODA/FD: OBST Q-Code=
 rule covers Q-Codes we know refer to obstacles, the FD: Obstacles (Keyword=
) rule looks at some Q-Codes that sometimes contain obstacles and checks fo=
r certain key words before filing them as obstacles.

AIP Web addresses - See below for a table of countries with freely accessib=
le AIPs that we sweep for changes.


Kind Regards,


Alex


